cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on network selection in integrated cellular and Wi-Fi networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper formulates the network selection problem as a Bayesian network selection game, which is a type of game theory. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers the impacts of network congestion and switching penalties, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a distributed network selection algorithm, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions user quality of experience, which is related to multimedia applications.
